   FWIW, I gather 2 second averages from my router @ home, and the average bandwidth that EQ uses is AROUND 1.5 kbytes a sec.. thats about 12kbits a second per active user.  If there's 40 servers, each with 1000 people on... That's an average bandwidth usage of 485760000 kbits/sec, which is ALOT of bandwidth... to the tune of 465MBits a second.  This is of course, averages.  Verant must be prepared for burstyness (heh right)... so lets just say that they have 600MBits a second of available bandwidth shared amongst all of the servers.  That's the equivilent of ~13 T3's, or ~4 OC-3's.... Well... as best as I can tell, a loaded OC3 goes for about 50k/month these days, so I guess a few hundred K/month for bandwidth isnt as bad as I had originally thought <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Nevermind, we're getting GANKED <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  hahaha (kidding) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uthommushom.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Thommus HoM</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#333333>(3/27/02 6:21:42 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fnamelesstaverngeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8078.topic&index=47>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Can you say Money Grab</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> &quot;I think your grasp of basic math leaves something to be desired.&quot;<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
